equation_narrative.headline: Polar representation assembles early, Q-specific prediction channels activate decisively at L30
equation_narrative.story: Position 49 in ubiquitin sits in a surface-exposed loop between beta-strand and helix. Through layers 1-23, the model assembles a representation consistent with polar residues (S, N, T oscillate in the logit lens at 10-26%), reading 4 structural contacts and 4 co-evolving positions. The representation character remains polar but non-specific through L23. At L30, Q-specific prediction channels activate explosively: F30:7328 (attention, 34.4 proj) and N30:732 (MLP, 0.96 proj for Q) drive probability from 7% to 51% in a single layer. By L33, Q reaches 98.14% confidence.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 build a polar representation through structural and co-evolutionary reading. Early features F1:5480 and F1:9146 (both 45+ proj) encode local sequence context around the IFAGK[Q]LEDGR motif. The logit lens oscillates between small polar residues (S peaks at 22.6% at L0, N reaches 26.4% at L6, T peaks at 22.4% at L8), reflecting the model's assembly of a polar-compatible context rather than specific predictions. Structural contacts (4 positions) and co-evolutionary signals (4 positions) flow in through layers 8-18, with F9:5728 (51.1 proj) and F18:6632 (20.2 proj) encoding spatial and evolutionary constraints. By L23, the representation is clearly polar-leaning (S at 14.7%, T at 19.3%) but lacks amino-acid-specific commitment.
perception_phase.context_character: Surface-exposed position in a loop region with polar character. Local sequence context is mixed (hydrophobic I/F/A/G upstream, charged K/E/D/R downstream). Moderate structural and co-evolutionary constraints favor polar residues without strong specificity.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 4 residues within 8Å, read primarily through L8-18 attention
Co-evolutionary coupling: 4 positions with correlated mutations, integrated through F9:2619 (46.7 proj) and F18:2075 (20.1 proj)
Local sequence: IFAGK upstream and LEDGR downstream encoded by F1:5480, F1:9146 (both 45+ proj)
Secondary structure context: Loop region between beta-strand and helix, encoded through F9:5728 (51.1 proj)

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes sharply at L30. Q-specific prediction channels activate: F30:7328 (attention, 34.4 proj) and F30:2678 (attention, 27.6 proj) drive Q from 7% to 51%. MLP neurons N30:732 (0.96 proj for Q specifically) and N30:16 (0.66 proj for Q) provide strong support. L31 consolidates with N31:1142 (0.68 proj) and L32 refines with N32:4536 (1.08 proj). By L33, F33:6423 (131.3 proj) and F33:4166 (126.5 proj) lock in Q at 98.14%.
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from perception to decision. At L23, the representation is diffuse (T at 19.3%, V at 8.3%, S at 14.7%) with no dominant candidate. At L24, F24:8676 (12.9 proj) and F24:459 (12.6 proj) begin to organize the representation toward specific amino acids, but Q remains weak (under 2%). L25-29 show gradual feature accumulation, then L30 triggers the decisive commitment with high-enrichment Q-specific features.

candidates.narrative: Q emerges decisively at L30, jumping from 7% to 51% in a single layer. F30:7328 (attention, 34.4 proj) and F30:2678 (attention, 27.6 proj) are Q-specific prediction channels that activate based on the polar context assembled in earlier layers. MLP neurons strongly support Q: N30:732 projects 0.96 specifically to Q, N30:16 adds 0.66, and N30:3370 contributes 0.65. L31-32 consolidate with N31:1142 (0.68 proj) and N32:4536 (1.08 proj). Final layer features F33:6423 (131.3 proj) and F33:4166 (126.5 proj) lock in 98.14% confidence.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges at L30 (7% → 51%), dominant by L31 (85%), final at L33 (98.14%)
key_evidence: F30:7328 (attn, 34.4 proj) — Q-specific prediction channel activates at L30
F33:6423 (attn, 131.3 proj) — final-layer Q commitment feature

candidates.narrative: S peaks at 22.6% in the embedding (L0), reflecting the representation's initial polar character based on local sequence. The logit lens shows S because the early representation encodes small-polar-residue compatibility, not because the model is predicting S. S remains visible through L23 (14.7%) as the polar representation persists, but collapses to 0.34% by L33 as Q-specific features dominate. S never activates amino-acid-specific prediction channels in the decision phase.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks at L0 (22.6%), visible through L23 (14.7%), eliminated by L30 (5.7%)
key_evidence: L0-L23: Logit lens reflects polar representation character, not S prediction
No S-specific features activate in L24-33 decision phase
Eliminated by Q-specific channels at L30

candidates.narrative: V shows an unusual late surge, peaking at 19.4% at L29 despite the polar context. This reflects transient activation of hydrophobic-voting neurons: N29:4781 projects 0.65 to L (hydrophobic) and 0.51 to Q, creating brief ambiguity. However, V lacks specific prediction channels and is rapidly suppressed by Q-specific features at L30. The V surge at L29 represents a momentary misalignment between MLP neuron votes and the overall polar context, quickly corrected by attention-driven Q channels.
key_evidence: N29:4781 (MLP, 0.51 proj to Q but 0.65 to L) — creates transient hydrophobic signal
L29 head 18 (structural eraser, -1.62 proj) — attempts to suppress but V briefly rises
No V-specific features in L30-33; eliminated by Q channels

candidates.narrative: T oscillates through the perception phase (peaks at 22.4% at L8, 19.3% at L23), reflecting the representation's polar character. Like S and N, T's early prominence is a logit-lens artifact of polar context assembly, not a prediction. T persists longer than S, reaching 19.3% at L29, but lacks specific prediction channels in the decision phase. T is suppressed by the same Q-specific features that eliminate other polar candidates, dropping to near-zero by L33.
key_evidence: L8 peak (22.4%) reflects polar representation, not T prediction
No T-specific features activate in L24-33
Suppressed by Q channels at L30-33

turning_points.description: The representation oscillates between small polar residues (N, S, T) as the model integrates structural and co-evolutionary information. Lead changes every 1-2 layers (N→L→N→T→N→S→N→S→V→N→S→V→T) reflect the model refining its understanding of the polar context without committing to a specific amino acid. This is perception-phase activity: the model is reading contacts, not making predictions. F9:5728 (51.1 proj) encodes spatial constraints, while F9:2619 (46.7 proj) integrates co-evolutionary signals.

The transition from perception to decision. At L23, the representation is diffuse (T 19.3%, S 14.7%, V 8.3%, Q only 1.9%) with total_answer_proj of -2.09 from MLPs, indicating the model has not yet committed. L24 shows first organization toward specific amino acids with F24:8676 (12.9 proj) and F24:459 (12.6 proj), though Q remains weak. L25 begins accumulating Q-compatible features, setting up the decisive L30 commitment. The key velocity event at L23 (total_delta -4.01, both attention and MLP driving away) represents the model clearing non-specific polar signal before committing.

Decisive Q commitment. L30 is the critical layer: Q jumps from 7% to 51% as F30:7328 (34.4 proj) and F30:2678 (27.6 proj) activate, while N30:732 (0.96 proj) and N30:16 (0.66 proj) provide MLP support. L31 consolidates (Q to 85%) with velocity event +7.99 (both attention and MLP driving toward Q). L32 refines with N32:4536 (1.08 proj) despite net negative MLP contribution (-5.26 total), showing attention-driven commitment overriding some MLP noise. L33 locks in 98.14% with F33:6423 (131.3 proj) and F33:4166 (126.5 proj).

deep_dives.label: Early context features L1-L9
deep_dives.caption: F1:5480 and F1:9146 (both 45+ proj) encode the local sequence context IFAGK[Q]LEDGR. F9:5728 (51.1 proj) integrates structural constraints from 4 contact positions. F9:2619 (46.7 proj) encodes co-evolutionary coupling to 4 distant positions. These features build the polar representation that persists through L23.

deep_dives.label: Polar representation L6-L18
deep_dives.caption: The logit lens oscillates between N, S, T (10-26%) as the model refines its understanding of the polar context. F9:5728 (51.1 proj) and F18:6632 (20.2 proj) show how structural and evolutionary information flows in. This is not the model 'changing its mind' — it's assembling a representation of what belongs here.

deep_dives.label: Perception→Decision L23-L24
deep_dives.caption: L23 shows diffuse polar representation (no dominant candidate). L24 features F24:8676 (12.9 proj) and F24:459 (12.6 proj) begin organizing toward specific amino acids. This is where the model shifts from 'what context is here' to 'what amino acid fits this context.'

deep_dives.label: MLP decision neurons L30-L32
deep_dives.caption: N30:732 (0.96 proj for Q) is the strongest Q-voting neuron, activating at the decisive L30 layer. N31:1142 (0.68 proj) and N32:4536 (1.08 proj) consolidate the decision. Note L32's net negative MLP contribution (-5.26 total) shows some neurons voting against Q, but attention-driven commitment overrides this noise.

deep_dives.label: Q-specific prediction channels L30-L33
deep_dives.caption: F30:7328 (34.4 proj) and F30:2678 (27.6 proj) are Q-specific prediction channels that activate at L30, driving Q from 7% to 51%. F33:6423 (131.3 proj) and F33:4166 (126.5 proj) lock in the final 98.14% confidence. These are high-enrichment features that fire specifically for Q given the assembled polar context.

deep_dives.label: Hydrophobic surge at L29
deep_dives.caption: V peaks at 19.4% at L29 despite the polar context. N29:4781 (0.51 proj to Q but 0.65 to L) creates transient hydrophobic signal. This represents momentary misalignment between MLP votes and the overall context, quickly corrected by Q-specific attention features at L30.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts Q with 98.14% confidence by assembling a polar surface-exposed context through layers 1-23, then activating Q-specific prediction channels at L30. The decisive evidence is the explosive activation of F30:7328 (34.4 proj) and N30:732 (0.96 proj), which recognize that the polar context with moderate structural/evolutionary constraints specifically requires Q rather than other polar residues (S, T, N). The early logit-lens oscillation between small polar residues was not indecision but rather the model systematically reading structural contacts and co-evolutionary signals to characterize the position's biochemical requirements before committing to the specific amino acid that best satisfies those requirements.
